      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "googlechat: add appPrincipal setup input + docs",
        "body": "Fixes #51694\n\n- Adds optional `appPrincipal` to the shared `ChannelSetupInput` type so `setup-core.ts` typechecks cleanly.\n- Keeps the existing patch scope for Google Chat app principal support and documentation.\n- Tests run: extensions/googlechat vitest suite + config:channels:check + config:docs:check + tsgo:test:extensions + git diff --check all pass.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Google Chat setup did not accept or expose `appPrincipal` in the setup adapter patch; the wizard already prompted for it but the typed adapter dropped it because `ChannelSetupInput` lacked the field.\n- Real environment tested: macOS 15.4, Node v26.0.0, local OpenClaw checkout on branch alex/51694-googlechat-app-principal-docs.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: `npx tsx -e \"import { googlechatSetupAdapter } from './extensions/googlechat/src/setup-core.ts'; console.log(JSON.stringify(googlechatSetupAdapter.applyAccountConfig({ cfg: { channels: { googlechat: {} } }, accountId: 'default', input: { name: 'Default', tokenFile: '/tmp/sa.json', appPrincipal: '123456789012345678901', audienceType: 'app-url', audience: 'https://example.com/googlechat' } }), null, 2));\"`\n- Evidence after fix: Terminal output showed the patched config object included `\"appPrincipal\": \"123456789012345678901\"` alongside the other fields.\n- Observed result after fix: `googlechatSetupAdapter.applyAccountConfig` accepts and forwards `appPrincipal` into the channel config, proving the changed setup behavior works end-to-end without mocks or CI only.\n- What was not tested: No live Google Chat API call or actual webhook delivery; only the local setup adapter behavior was exercised.\n",
        "branch": "alex/51694-googlechat-app-principal-docs",
